main event: An unidentified object was observed in Santa Monica, California on August 25, 1969, identified as the decay of Cosmos 294 Rocket Body.
interesting points: The object was visually observed from the ground at 1930 PDT.,The sighting lasted for approximately 1-2 minutes.,The object's trajectory was moving in a southerly direction., The source of the sighting was reported as military.,Physical evidence was noted to be present.
sighted object: unidentified object identified as a satellite decay
witness description: The observer was a male with 17 years of experience as a USAF pilot.
